{"id":2067,"date":"2022-10-01T14:19:45","date_gmt":"2022-10-01T14:19:45","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/?page_id=2067"},"modified":"2023-04-29T07:36:42","modified_gmt":"2023-04-29T07:36:42","slug":"breakoutfolder","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/sandboxie\/breakoutfolder\/","title":{"rendered":"Breakout Folder"},"content":{"rendered":"<h1>Breakout Folder<\/h1>\n<p><em>BreakoutFolder<\/em>  is a sandbox setting in <a href=\"SandboxieIni\">Sandboxie Ini<\/a> available since v1.0.8 \/ 5.55.8. It forces a folder's content to run unsandboxed even if started from inside the sandbox.<\/p>\n<p>Usage:<\/p>\n<pre><code>   .\n   .\n   .\n   [DefaultBox]\n   BreakoutFolder=C:\\Downloads\n   BreakoutFolder=E:\\\n   BreakoutFolder=C:\\App\\*\n   BreakoutFolder=C:\\App?\n   BreakoutFolder=C:\\?pp\\*<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>The first example specifies that any content inside the folder &quot;C:\\Downloads&quot; will be launched unsandboxed.<\/p>\n<p>Entire drives can also be specified as shown in the second example.<\/p>\n<p>The third and fourth lines show basic characters from wildcards.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>*<\/code> defines any subfolder beyond App folder (App\\1, App\\1\\1 and etc.).<\/li>\n<li><code>?<\/code> defines a single character from folder (Appa, App8 and etc.) but not subfolders.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Also, you can combine several wildcards to match the specified folder name and subfolders.<\/p>\n<p>NOTE:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Shortcuts that link to a program outside the specified folders will be launched sandboxed. For example: if you place a shortcut inside a broken out folder and it links to some program in a non broken out folder, then the shortcut will launch sandboxed.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Check <a href=\"BreakoutProcess\">BreakoutProcess<\/a> for information on breaking out programs.<\/p>\n<p>Also check <a href=\"ForceFolder\">ForceFolder<\/a>, the counterpart of this setting, which forces a folder's content to launch sandboxed.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Breakout Folder BreakoutFolder is a sandbox setting in Sandboxie Ini available since v1.0.8 \/ 5.55.8. It forces a folder&#8217;s content to run unsandboxed even if started from inside the sandbox. Usage: . . . [DefaultBox] BreakoutFolder=C:\\Downloads BreakoutFolder=E:\\ BreakoutFolder=C:\\App\\* BreakoutFolder=C:\\App? BreakoutFolder=C:\\?pp\\* The first example specifies that any content inside the folder &quot;C:\\Downloads&quot; will be launched unsandboxed. &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/sandboxie\/breakoutfolder\/\" class=\"more-link\">Continue reading <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Breakout Folder<\/span> <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":108,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2067"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2067"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2067\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2282,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2067\/revisions\/2282"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/108"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2067"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}